Definition: the power or right to give orders or make decisions
Example: he has the authority to issue warrants; deputies are given authorization to make arrests; a place of potency in the state
Synonyms: authorization, authorisation, potency, adj, all, powerful, potent, dominance, verb, social, dominate, say-so, control, the, power, or, right, to, give, orders, make, decisions, he, has, issue, warrants, deputies, are, given, arrests, a, place, of, in, state
Category: noun.attribute
